{
  "text": "The global temporal changes in gene expression following MCAO in the stroke model are dominated by the top three eigensystems (Figure 2A ). The eigengene of the first eigensystem in the MCAO dataset (M1, \"M\" to indicate MCAO) is constant in time (data not shown) in the log-expression space and thus represents the average level of expression across all the conditions. The second eigengene (M2) represents an increased expression, as compared to control value, at 12-48 h following MCAO, with a peak at 12 h ( Figure 2B ). The third eigengene (M3) represents a complex pattern with an increase in gene expression at 12 h followed by down-regulation of expression at 24 h and further drop at 48 h ( Figure 2C ). Notably, the three top eigengenes indicate no changes in gene expression at 6 h after MCAO, which is in agreement with our earlier PCR results showing no changes in mRNA levels of a smaller number of genes [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "38897028"
